README.md
     1вҶ’semver(1) -- The semantic versioner for npm
     4вҶ’## Install
     6вҶ’```bash
     7вҶ’npm install semver
     8вҶ’````
     9вҶ’
    10вҶ’## Usage
    12вҶ’As a node module:
    13вҶ’
    14вҶ’```js
    15вҶ’const semver = require('semver')
    16вҶ’
    17вҶ’semver.valid('1.2.3') // '1.2.3'
    18вҶ’semver.valid('a.b.c') // null
    19вҶ’semver.clean('  =v1.2.3   ') // '1.2.3'
    20вҶ’semver.satisfies('1.2.3', '1.x || >=2.5.0 || 5.0.0 - 7.2.3') // true
    21вҶ’semver.gt('1.2.3', '9.8.7') // false
    22вҶ’semver.lt('1.2.3', '9.8.7') // true
    23вҶ’semver.minVersion('>=1.0.0') // '1.0.0'
    24вҶ’semver.valid(semver.coerce('v2')) // '2.0.0'
    25вҶ’semver.valid(semver.coerce('42.6.7.9.3-alpha')) // '42.6.7'
    26вҶ’```
    27вҶ’
    28вҶ’You can also just load the module for the function that you care about if
    29вҶ’you'd like to minimize your footprint.
    30вҶ’
    31вҶ’```js
    32вҶ’// load the whole API at once in a single object
    33вҶ’const semver = require('semver')
    34вҶ’
    35вҶ’// or just load the bits you need
    36вҶ’// all of them listed here, just pick and choose what you want
    37вҶ’
    38вҶ’// classes
    39вҶ’const SemVer = require('semver/classes/semver')
    40вҶ’const Comparator = require('semver/classes/comparator')
    41вҶ’const Range = require('semver/classes/range')
    42вҶ’
    43вҶ’// functions for working with versions
    44вҶ’const semverParse = require('semver/functions/parse')
    45вҶ’const semverValid = require('semver/functions/valid')
    46вҶ’const semverClean = require('semver/functions/clean')
    47вҶ’const semverInc = require('semver/functions/inc')
    48вҶ’const semverDiff = require('semver/functions/diff')
    49вҶ’const semverMajor = require('semver/functions/major')
    50вҶ’const semverMinor = require('semver/functions/minor')
    51вҶ’const semverPatch = require('semver/functions/patch')
    52вҶ’const semverPrerelease = require('semver/functions/prerelease')
    53вҶ’const semverCompare = require('semver/functions/compare')
    54вҶ’const semverRcompare = require('semver/functions/rcompare')
    55вҶ’const semverCompareLoose = require('semver/functions/compare-loose')
    56вҶ’const semverCompareBuild = require('semver/functions/compare-build')
    57вҶ’const semverSort = require('semver/functions/sort')
    58вҶ’const semverRsort = require('semver/functions/rsort')
    59вҶ’
    60вҶ’// low-level comparators between versions
    61вҶ’const semverGt = require('semver/functions/gt')
    62вҶ’const semverLt = require('semver/functions/lt')
    63вҶ’const semverEq = require('semver/functions/eq')
    64вҶ’const semverNeq = require('semver/functions/neq')
    65вҶ’const semverGte = require('semver/functions/gte')
    66вҶ’const semverLte = require('semver/functions/lte')
    67вҶ’const semverCmp = require('semver/functions/cmp')
    68вҶ’const semverCoerce = require('semver/functions/coerce')
    69вҶ’
    70вҶ’// working with ranges
    71вҶ’const semverSatisfies = require('semver/functions/satisfies')
    72вҶ’const semverMaxSatisfying = require('semver/ranges/max-satisfying')
    73вҶ’const semverMinSatisfying = require('semver/ranges/min-satisfying')
    74вҶ’const semverToComparators = require('semver/ranges/to-comparators')
    75вҶ’const semverMinVersion = require('semver/ranges/min-version')
    76вҶ’const semverValidRange = require('semver/ranges/valid')
    77вҶ’const semverOutside = require('semver/ranges/outside')
    78вҶ’const semverGtr = require('semver/ranges/gtr')
    79вҶ’const semverLtr = require('semver/ranges/ltr')
    80вҶ’const semverIntersects = require('semver/ranges/intersects')
    81вҶ’const semverSimplifyRange = require('semver/ranges/simplify')
    82вҶ’const semverRangeSubset = require('semver/ranges/subset')
    83вҶ’```
    84вҶ’
    85вҶ’As a command-line utility:
    86вҶ’
    87вҶ’```
    88вҶ’$ semver -h
    89вҶ’
    90вҶ’A JavaScript implementation of the https://semver.org/ specification
    91вҶ’Copyright Isaac Z. Schlueter
    92вҶ’
    93вҶ’Usage: semver [options] <version> [<version> [...]]
    94вҶ’Prints valid versions sorted by SemVer precedence
    95вҶ’
    96вҶ’Options:
    97вҶ’-r --range <range>
    98вҶ’        Print versions that match the specified range.
    99вҶ’
   100вҶ’-i --increment [<level>]
   101вҶ’        Increment a version by the specified level.  Level can
   102вҶ’        be one of: major, minor, patch, premajor, preminor,
   103вҶ’        prepatch, prerelease, or release.  Default level is 'patch'.
   104вҶ’        Only one version may be specified.
   105вҶ’
   106вҶ’--preid <identifier>
   107вҶ’        Identifier to be used to prefix premajor, preminor,
   108вҶ’        prepatch or prerelease version increments.
   109вҶ’
   110вҶ’-l --loose
   111вҶ’        Interpret versions and ranges loosely
   112вҶ’
   113вҶ’-n <0|1|false>
   114вҶ’        Base number for prerelease identifier (default: 0).
   115вҶ’        Use false to omit the number altogether.
   116вҶ’
   117вҶ’-p --include-prerelease
   118вҶ’        Always include prerelease versions in range matching
   119вҶ’
   120вҶ’-c --coerce
   121вҶ’        Coerce a string into SemVer if possible
   122вҶ’        (does not imply --loose)
   123вҶ’
   124вҶ’--rtl
   125вҶ’        Coerce version strings right to left
   126вҶ’
   127вҶ’--ltr
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   139вҶ’## Versions
   141вҶ’A "version" is described by the `v2.0.0` specification found at
   142вҶ’<https://semver.org/>.
   143вҶ’
   144вҶ’A leading `"="` or `"v"` character is stripped off and ignored.
   145вҶ’Support for stripping a leading "v" is kept for compatibility with `v1.0.0` of the SemVer
   146вҶ’specification but should not be used anymore.
   147вҶ’
   148вҶ’## Ranges
   150вҶ’A `version range` is a set of `comparators` that specify versions
   151вҶ’that satisfy the range.
   152вҶ’
   153вҶ’A `comparator` is composed of an `operator` and a `version`.  The set
   154вҶ’of primitive `operators` is:
   155вҶ’
   156вҶ’* `<` Less than
   157вҶ’* `<=` Less than or equal to
   158вҶ’* `>` Greater than
   159вҶ’* `>=` Greater than or equal to
   160вҶ’* `=` Equal.  If no operator is specified, then equality is assumed,
   161вҶ’  so this operator is optional but MAY be included.
   162вҶ’
   163вҶ’For example, the comparator `>=1.2.7` would match the versions
   164вҶ’`1.2.7`, `1.2.8`, `2.5.3`, and `1.3.9`, but not the versions `1.2.6`
   165вҶ’or `1.1.0`. The comparator `>1` is equivalent to `>=2.0.0` and
   166вҶ’would match the versions `2.0.0` and `3.1.0`, but not the versions
   167вҶ’`1.0.1` or `1.1.0`.
   168вҶ’
   169вҶ’Comparators can be joined by whitespace to form a `comparator set`,
   170вҶ’which is satisfied by the **intersection** of all of the comparators
   171вҶ’it includes.
   172вҶ’
   173вҶ’A range is composed of one or more comparator sets, joined by `||`.  A
   174вҶ’version matches a range if and only if every comparator in at least
   175вҶ’one of the `||`-separated comparator sets is satisfied by the version.
   176вҶ’
   177вҶ’For example, the range `>=1.2.7 <1.3.0` would match the versions
   178вҶ’`1.2.7`, `1.2.8`, and `1.2.99`, but not the versions `1.2.6`, `1.3.0`,
   179вҶ’or `1.1.0`.
   180вҶ’
   181вҶ’The range `1.2.7 || >=1.2.9 <2.0.0` would match the versions `1.2.7`,
   182вҶ’`1.2.9`, and `1.4.6`, but not the versions `1.2.8` or `2.0.0`.
   183вҶ’
   184вҶ’### Prerelease Tags
   186вҶ’If a version has a prerelease tag (for example, `1.2.3-alpha.3`) then
   187вҶ’it will only be allowed to satisfy comparator sets if at least one
   188вҶ’comparator with the same `[major, minor, patch]` tuple also has a
      вҶ’вҖҰ
