   250вҶ’#### Prerelease Identifier Base
   252вҶ’The method `.inc` takes an optional parameter 'identifierBase' string
   253вҶ’that will let you let your prerelease number as zero-based or one-based.
   254вҶ’Set to `false` to omit the prerelease number altogether.
   255вҶ’If you do not specify this parameter, it will default to zero-based.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   279вҶ’### Advanced Range Syntax
   281вҶ’Advanced range syntax desugars to primitive comparators in
   282вҶ’deterministic ways.
   283вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   287вҶ’#### Hyphen Ranges `X.Y.Z - A.B.C`
   289вҶ’Specifies an inclusive set.
   290вҶ’
   291вҶ’* `1.2.3 - 2.3.4` := `>=1.2.3 <=2.3.4`
   292вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   306вҶ’#### X-Ranges `1.2.x` `1.X` `1.2.*` `*`
   308вҶ’Any of `X`, `x`, or `*` may be used to "stand in" for one of the
   309вҶ’numeric values in the `[major, minor, patch]` tuple.
   310вҶ’
   311вҶ’* `*` := `>=0.0.0` (Any non-prerelease version satisfies, unless
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   324вҶ’#### Tilde Ranges `~1.2.3` `~1.2` `~1`
   326вҶ’Allows patch-level changes if a minor version is specified on the
   327вҶ’comparator.  Allows minor-level changes if not.
   328вҶ’
   329вҶ’* `~1.2.3` := `>=1.2.3 <1.(2+1).0` := `>=1.2.3 <1.3.0-0`
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   341вҶ’#### Caret Ranges `^1.2.3` `^0.2.5` `^0.0.4`
   343вҶ’Allows changes that do not modify the left-most non-zero element in the
   344вҶ’`[major, minor, patch]` tuple.  In other words, this allows patch and
   345вҶ’minor updates for versions `1.0.0` and above, patch updates for
   346вҶ’versions `0.X >=0.1.0`, and *no* updates for versions `0.0.X`.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   384вҶ’### Range Grammar
   386вҶ’Putting all this together, here is a Backus-Naur grammar for ranges,
   387вҶ’for the benefit of parser authors:
   388вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   408вҶ’## Functions
   410вҶ’All methods and classes take a final `options` object argument.  All
   411вҶ’options in this object are `false` by default.  The options supported
   412вҶ’are:
   413вҶ’
   414вҶ’- `loose`: Be more forgiving about not-quite-valid semver strings.
   415вҶ’  (Any resulting output will always be 100% strict compliant, of
   416вҶ’  course.)  For backwards compatibility reasons, if the `options`
   417вҶ’  argument is a boolean value instead of an object, it is interpreted
   418вҶ’  to be the `loose` param.
   419вҶ’- `includePrerelease`: Set to suppress the [default
   420вҶ’  behavior](https://github.com/npm/node-semver#prerelease-tags) of
   421вҶ’  excluding prerelease tagged versions from ranges unless they are
   422вҶ’  explicitly opted into.
   423вҶ’
   424вҶ’Strict-mode Comparators and Ranges will be strict about the SemVer
   425вҶ’strings that they parse.
   426вҶ’
   427вҶ’* `valid(v)`: Return the parsed version, or null if it's not valid.
   428вҶ’* `inc(v, releaseType, options, identifier, identifierBase)`: 
   429вҶ’  Return the version incremented by the release
   430вҶ’  type (`major`, `premajor`, `minor`, `preminor`, `patch`,
   431вҶ’  `prepatch`, `prerelease`, or `release`), or null if it's not valid
   432вҶ’  * `premajor` in one call will bump the version up to the next major
   433вҶ’    version and down to a prerelease of that major version.
   434вҶ’    `preminor`, and `prepatch` work the same way.
   435вҶ’  * If called from a non-prerelease version, `prerelease` will work the
   436вҶ’    same as `prepatch`. It increments the patch version and then makes a
   437вҶ’    prerelease. If the input version is already a prerelease it simply
   438вҶ’    increments it.
   439вҶ’  * `release` will remove any prerelease part of the version.
   440вҶ’  * `identifier` can be used to prefix `premajor`, `preminor`,
   441вҶ’    `prepatch`, or `prerelease` version increments. `identifierBase`
   442вҶ’    is the base to be used for the `prerelease` identifier.
   443вҶ’* `prerelease(v)`: Returns an array of prerelease components, or null
   444вҶ’  if none exist. Example: `prerelease('1.2.3-alpha.1') -> ['alpha', 1]`
   445вҶ’* `major(v)`: Return the major version number.
   446вҶ’* `minor(v)`: Return the minor version number.
   447вҶ’* `patch(v)`: Return the patch version number.
   448вҶ’* `intersects(r1, r2, loose)`: Return true if the two supplied ranges
   449вҶ’  or comparators intersect.
   450вҶ’* `parse(v)`: Attempt to parse a string as a semantic version, returning either
   451вҶ’  a `SemVer` object or `null`.
   452вҶ’
   453вҶ’### Comparison
   455вҶ’* `gt(v1, v2)`: `v1 > v2`
   456вҶ’* `gte(v1, v2)`: `v1 >= v2`
   457вҶ’* `lt(v1, v2)`: `v1 < v2`
